-- Siemens to decide on Alstom offer after meeting with Hollande
-- By Maria Sheahan
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 08:16AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, April 28 (Reuters) - Germany's Siemens <SIEGn.DE> said in a statement on Monday its board would convene as soon as possible following a meeting with French President Francois Hollande to decide whether to make an offer for Alstom <ALSO.PA> and what this would consist of.

Three people familiar with the matter earlier told Reuters that Siemens' supervisory board would discuss a possible deal with Alstom at an extraordinary meeting on Tuesday. [ID:nWEB00M5Y]